Adjust rack to middle position (middle and top for 4 servings) and preheat #oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}, @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon}, a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place on one side of a #baking sheet{} (for 4 servings, spread out across entire sheet).

Evenly brush tops of chicken breasts with @sour cream{2%tablespoon}. Mound coated sides with panko mixture, pressing to adhere.

Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Toss broccoli on opposite side of sheet from chicken with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (For 4 servings, toss broccoli on a second #sheet{}.)

Roast on middle rack until chicken is crispy and cooked through and broccoli is tender and lightly browned at the edges, ~{15-20%minutes}. (For 4, roast chicken on middle rack and broccoli on top rack.)

> Broccoli may finish before chicken—if so, remove from oven and continue roasting chicken.

Meanwhile, halve @demi-baguette{1} lengthwise. When chicken has 5 minutes left, toast baguette in #oven or #toaster oven{} until lightly golden.

Spread cut sides of baguette with @garlic herb butter{2%tablespoon}.

Divide chicken, broccoli, and garlic bread between plates. Serve.